## Instructions
Return NEW filter values to add to the pool — values NOT already listed above. Add several across the families; each new value becomes another axis the search can combine, opening adjacent regions.

- **Learn from the qualified leads.** Their real titles, seniorities, locations, departments and functions are the pattern that works — propose values adjacent to them (sibling titles, neighbouring seniorities, the same function in a nearby country). If none have qualified yet, generalize from the product and target.
- **Use only real-world values a lead database would actually hold** — plain department and function names (`Sales`, `Marketing`, `Human Resources`), real job titles, and real COUNTRY names. Every field except `lead_seniority` is free text matched against a search index, so an invented or misspelled value is not rejected — it simply matches ZERO leads and wastes a search.
- `lead_location` takes **countries**, never regions. `Europe`, `EMEA`, `Eastern Europe` match zero leads.
- `lead_seniority` must be one of the fixed levels: {{ seniorities|join(", ") }}.
- Do NOT repeat values already in the pool. Do NOT propose headcount — the size band is fixed.
- Prefer a handful of strong, specific additions over a long hedged list.
